Operculum semicircular; dorsal and lateral margin well developed, smooth; ventral margin (opercular ridge) with 8 – 13 pairs of stout and golden paleae, curved dorsally, with blunt tips (
Figs 22A – C
;
23A – B
).

First pair of tentacular cirri not extending beyond tips of paleae, with annuli, arising from connection of opercular margin and paleal ridge (
Figs 22B, F
; 
23A
). Pair of small ventral lappets present behind tentacular cirri near cephalic veil on segment 1 (

Figs 22C 
–
D

; 
